22/12/2002
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- Yugoslavia announced Friday (20 December) that it has agreed to open its airspace to NATO. Foreign Minister Goran Svilanovic and NATO Secretary General George Robertson exchanged letters allowing alliance aircraft supporting missions in the Balkans to fly over Yugoslav territory. The foreign ministry issued a statement saying it regards the agreement as "a major step towards rapprochement." (AP, AFP, Tanjug - 20/12/02)
